{
  "prompt": "Side profile technical drawing of an electric bicycle with the following features: - Front wheel is 26-inch with an on-road tire and air suspension fork - Rear wheel is 20-inch with a wide 3.0-inch CST Big Boat tire - Rear mono-shock suspension system inspired by motorcycle swingarm design, with a single shock absorber mounted diagonally between the frame and rear swingarm - Frame is step-through style, chrome silver color - Central mid-drive motor with belt drive connected to rear wheel - Battery mounted along the downtube - Rear rack installed for delivery purposes. Clean technical-style drawing with visible components, realistic proportions, and neutral background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A clean technical diagram comparing the frame geometry of two electric bicycles, side view. Both frames are identical except for wheel sizes. Left: front wheel is 26-inch Schwalbe Marathon tire (approx. 660mm outer diameter), rear wheel is 20-inch CST Big Boat 3.0 (approx. 540mm outer diameter). Right: both wheels are 20-inch CST Big Boat tires. Show bottom bracket height difference, head tube angle change, and overall frame tilt. Use labeled lines and annotations for visual clarity. The bikes should have visible shocks and the same frame shape.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
